{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:53:08.046Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The original Transformer paired an "}, {"type": "text", "text": "encoder", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " (bidirectional context) with a "}, {"type": "text", "text": "decoder", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " (autoregressive generation with cross-attention to encoder states). Most agent LLMs today are "}, {"type": "text", "text": "decoder-only", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ", but encoder\u2013decoder designs still appear in translation, summarization, and some tool-augmented pipelines\u2014so the split remains foundational."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Encoder-decoder vs decoder-only transformer architecture comparison with attention patterns"}}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoder stack", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 self-attention over input; builds rich representations of source text (e.g., retrieved docs)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decoder stack", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 masked self-attention plus cross-attention to encoder outputs; generates target tokens one step at a time"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-attention", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 queries from decoder, keys and values from encoder; lets each generated token consult the full source"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decoder-only GPT-style models fold \"encoding\" and \"decoding\" into one causal stack: the prompt is processed with causal masking during prefill, then generation continues autoregressively. Encoder\u2013decoder models separate "}, {"type": "text", "text": "reading", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " from "}, {"type": "text", "text": "writing", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": "\u2014useful when the input is long and fixed (knowledge base) and output is short (JSON action)."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How it works"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoder layer:  SelfAttn \u2192 FFN  (bidirectional)\nDecoder layer:  MaskedSelfAttn \u2192 CrossAttn(encoder) \u2192 FFN\nCross-attention: Q from decoder, K/V from encoder memory"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Comparison"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoder\u2013decoder (T5, BART)", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 strong for seq2seq; two stacks to train and serve"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decoder-only (GPT, LLaMA)", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 one stack; prompt+completion unified; dominates agent APIs"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoder-only (BERT)", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " \u2014 understanding tasks; not used for open-ended generation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Agentic AI connection"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hosted agent APIs are almost always decoder-only chat models. Patterns mimic encoder\u2013decoder behavior: RAG puts retrieved text early in context (encoded jointly with the query), then the model generates actions\u2014a single causal pass rather than two-module architecture. Separate reranker encoders (BERT-style) plus decoder LLMs are a hybrid production pattern."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to use encoder\u2013decoder"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fixed large corpus input with structured short output"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Legacy fine-tuned T5/BART pipelines"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Some multimodal models use cross-attention from text decoder to vision encoder"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoder builds source representations; decoder generates with cross-attention"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decoder-only LLMs unify both roles in one causal model"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-attention is the template for \"consult external memory while generating\""}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Agent design often simulates encoder\u2013decoder via prompt layout and retrieval"}]}]}]}]}}